---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ClaritySeries from "../components/ClaritySeries.astro";
---

<Layout
  metaDescription="StephBe founder's story: experience in HR and leadership; delivering coaching, workshops and strategic leadership programmes to help organisations regain clarity and performance."
  metaKeywords="StephBe, leadership, coaching, organisational development, executive coaching, leadership development"
  title="My Approach — StephBe"
  ogUrl="https://stephbe.ie/my-approach/"
  classMain="my-story"
>
  <section class="hero-section">
    <h1>My Approach</h1>
  </section>
  <section class="about-me">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="text">
        <h3>Helping people see what they couldn't see before.</h3>
        <p>
          My work is filled with variety.​ <br />
          Some days I'm coaching a leader through a career-defining decision.​ <br />
          Some days I'm helping an executive team navigate organisational change.​ <br />
          Some days I'm standing on a stage speaking to hundreds of people.
        </p>
        <h3>My purpose never changes.​</h3>
        <p>I help people think differently so they can perform differently. Behaviour follows mindset.​</p>
        <div>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-left.svg" alt="" />
          <span>"You don't rely on generic coaching frameworks. You help people think differently."</span>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-right.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
        <h3>Clarity changes everything.​</h3>
        <p>
          People come to me with a strategy problem, a communication problem, a team or change issue.​ <br /> Often, they're
          looking at the challenge through a lens that no longer serves them.​ <br />I create the clarity that allows
          people to see what's really happening. Once thinking changes, behaviour follows. Meaningful change begins
          here.
        </p>
        <div>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-left.svg" alt="" />
          <span>Steph has an incredible ability to help people see the woods for the trees.​</span>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-right.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
        <h3>Looking beneath the surface​</h3>
        <p>
          I've never been interested in surface-level solutions. I'm curious about what's underneath. The beliefs people
          hold, what they're avoiding, the patterns that shape behaviour, the assumptions that have become invisible.​ <br
          />
          Whether I'm working with one person or one thousand, I'm looking for the same thing.
        </p>
        <h3>What's really driving this?​</h3>
        <p>
          Because when we understand the real issue, we can stop treating symptoms and start creating lasting change.​
        </p>
        <div>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-left.svg" alt="" />
          <span>"Steph consistently moves beyond reflection into meaningful action."​</span>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-right.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
        <h3>My approach​</h3>
        <p>
          I don't arrive with a one-size-fits-all framework. I meet people where they are, create safe spaces for honest
          conversations, and help them see new possibilities.​ Clients often describe my work as energetic, engaging and
          practical, we turn insight into action which creates lasting change.
        </p>
        <div>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-left.svg" alt="" />
          <span>“You develop confidence without dependency."​</span>
          <img src="../../public/icons/quote-right.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="my-background">
        <dl>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="bg1">
                Professional Background <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg1" class="active">
              <ul>
                <li>Former Head of HR in international organisations</li>
                <li>Strategic leadership advisor and Executive Coach</li>
                <li>Speaker on leadership, clarity and organisational performance</li>
              </ul>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg2">
                Advanced Diploma in Personal and Business Coaching
                <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg2">Irish Life Coaching Institute, 2024</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg3">
                Advanced Diploma in Coaching with Neuroscience
                <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg3">The Positive Success Group</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg4">
                Diploma in Personal and Business Coaching <img
                  src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg"
                  alt="Toggle details"
                />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg4">Irish Life Coaching Institute, 2020</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg5">
                Certificate in Career Coaching <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg5">Irish Life Coaching Institute, 2020</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg6">
                Certificate in Training Delivery and Evaluation <img
                  src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg"
                  alt="Toggle details"
                />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg6">(QQI Level 6) 2021</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg7">
                CIPD Certificate in Personnel Practice <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg7">Dublin Institute of Technology, 2005</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>
              <button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bg8">
                Bachelor of Business (2:1) <img src="../public/icons/arrow-down.svg" alt="Toggle details" />
              </button>
            </dt>
            <dd id="bg8">Dublin Business School, 2004</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="img">
      <img src="../public/img/my-story/my-story.JPG" alt="Portrait of StephBe in professional setting" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="clarity-series">
    <div class="clarity-series-content">
      <div class="cs-content">
        <h3>The StephBe Global Collective​</h3>
      <p>
        Over the years I've built a trusted network of exceptional specialists across leadership, organisational
        development, HR, coaching, facilitation, learning design and communications.​
      </p>
      <p>
        When a project benefits from additional expertise, I bring together the right people to create the greatest
        impact for my clients.​
      </p>
      <p>
        Every member of the StephBe Global Collective is someone I've worked with, trust completely and would happily
        recommend.​
      </p>
      <p>
        It's a flexible model that means clients receive the personal relationship of working directly with me, backed
        by the capability of a wider team when needed.
      </p>
      </div>

      <section class="rhythm-section container">
        <div class="rhythms">
          <div class="rhythm">
            <h4>Where it started​</h4>
            <p>
              Over the past twenty years I've worked across organisations of different sizes and sectors, leading people
              functions, supporting leadership teams and helping organisations navigate growth, change and complexity.
              Along the way I discovered something that has shaped everything I do today:
            </p>
            <p>
              The biggest shifts happen when people start asking better questions, give and gain clarity, and manage the
              organisational nervous system.​
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rhythm">
            <h4>Continually learning​</h4>
            <p>
              I'm endlessly curious about how people think, perform and change. That curiosity has led me to continue
              studying throughout my career, including advanced qualifications in coaching and occupational
              neuroscience.
            </p>
            <p>
              I continue challenging my own thinking, so I can better support the people and organisations I work with.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rhythm">
            <h4>Let's start with a conversation​</h4>
            <p>
              Whether you're leading an organisation through change, developing your leadership team, or simply looking
              for a different perspective, I'd love to hear what's on your mind . Sometimes one conversation is all it
              takes to see things differently.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="cs-btn">
        <a
          class="btn-third"
          data-cal-link="stephbe/catch-up"
          data-cal-namespace="catch-up"
          data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book a Clarity Conversation</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="responsibility">
    <h2>Responsibility</h2>
    <p>
      The money, opportunity and innovation left on the table when human potential goes untapped matters not just
      commercially, but humanly. When people invite me into their organisations, teams or leadership challenges, they’re
      trusting me with something important. I don’t take that lightly. If this way of working resonates, then we’re
      already having the right conversation.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
